benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/tags - Add tags to account

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05 cover successful creation with one or more tags.
Invalid Payload: TC07 (empty body), TC08 (malformed body), TC09 (invalid tag IDs format), TC17 (extra unexpected parameters) cover malformed or invalid inputs.
Duplicate Submission: TC19 tests duplicates within request and ensures only unique tags are created.
Large Payloads: TC18 tests handling of large number of tag definitions in payload.
Validation: TC09, TC10 cover invalid/non-existent tag definitions and missing required header scenarios.
Authorization: TC11 tests missing required header (401/400 variants).
Server Error Handling: TC16 covers system/service unavailability leading to 503, TC15 covers unauthorized access scenario (401).

Edge Case Coverage: TC12 (missing accountId), TC13 (invalid accountId format), TC14 (non-existent account), TC22 (header injection), TC23 (special characters in tag definitions), TC24 (API version backward compatibility).
Concurrency: TC21 tests concurrent requests handling and deduplication.
Boundary/Limit Testing: TC20 tests performance-ish timing constraint (2 seconds).
gaps: Pagination/Query Parameters: POST tests do not explore pagination behavior on the response for very large tag sets beyond TC18.
Caching Behavior: No tests validating caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control).
Rate Limiting/Throttling: No tests to validate behavior under rate limiting or bursts.
Different Status Codes Diversity: Some edge cases expect 400 for various client errors; explicit 403 for forbidden access is not tested.
Detailed error payload structure: While many tests assert presence of error messages, not all specify exact error payload schemas across all failure types.
recommendations: Add explicit tests for rate limiting and throttling behavior on POST /tags.
Add tests asserting 403 Forbidden for unauthorized access with proper token but insufficient permissions.
Add caching header verification (ETag, Cache-Control) for successful responses.
Add pagination-related tests for POST when server supports paging of created tag resources in responses, including large payloads beyond 100 items.
Extend error payload schema validation to ensure consistent error structures across all 4xx/5xx responses.
